title: Do you think you can be anything you want to be? - Quora

response.answer_text: The key word in this question is: “Think”. Without that effort first, nothing will transpire in anyones life. Without the forethought, or with a desire…nothing will ever happen. Thinking you would like to be something..a doctor, a teacher, a truck driver, or any other job or career you put into your own mind…can be brought forward into anyones life. This is what and how dreams are made into reality…and if the drive to head towards that dream is strong…somehow, some way, it will come true. But this does not mean every dream will come true and it does not mean the goal you set for yourself is possible. A persons mindset…how they see themselves and how they truly are is also a vast area to understand. In my own life…I wanted to be many things…from Conservation Officer, to RCMP, to a Vet, and even to crew on the big tugs that worked the Fraser River…but this just never seemed to unfold and for some reason or another, none of those desires were ever strong enough within me to do so. Every person has their own shortfalls…this is not bad nor a judgement…it is a fact. What I may be good in, you might find trivial and those who work hard in Universities..and get ‘letters’ and a title for their names deserve those ‘letters’. But this does not in anyway make them superior to other peoples work. Everything from blue collar, white collar, no collar jobs, most times just comes along and we just go along for the ride until such time as we are successful in those positions. Life on the other hand might deal us cards that are indeed difficult to go around, to get an education, to even afford a higher education. Many fields are beyond my comprehension…and I will make no apologies for not having the brain power to have gone into any fields where the work for me was very difficult…sometimes too difficult. What others take in stride…I needed to live fully immersed in…I needed to train myself to understand and finally to actually accomplish the tasks in front of me. Thus I never did get a degree of any sort and though I tried many things…some I was able to master and others…well, not so much. The point here for me is that regardless of who, where, when, you were born, life sometimes is difficult, and in that difficulty…somewhere deep inside if a desire is strong enough…the path will open to further that desire. Desire is a tool that shows us something we don’t have but we are drive to get. I suppose desire is a “Lack” tool…of knowing we don’t have something and go to find whatever that something is…a degree…a blue collar job…a white collar job or to even open your own business. Some people are good at building, others at cooking, while others feel the need to help others…nurses and doctors. Some will find that driving a truck long distance is acceptable in their lives…or to go into waste management. There are many jobs…electrical, computer technologies, lawyers, city workers and road builders…many diverse careers but without that one things…without that one push…a “desire” to find a job and maybe not a good one need to be present first. Sometimes we fall into some position…some job, but that does not mean it will be a career but only be a stepping stone to further that desire. So can anyone be whatever they want to be? That is up to the individual to head towards their own determined desire, or they can just give up and go with the flow of their lives and accept that dreams are for other people. This point is an individual view and might not take into consideration all the variables of life, where you live, and who you are. In my life…I have done many different things, hard physical work, long hours, poor conditions, but something kept opening for me…little changes…lots of effort…then another little change. As I matured I found other avenues to explore and those other dreams I had…did not unfold nor did I succeed in making them real. What did happen was both caused by effort, of not accepting I couldn’t do something but knowing I had to make myself learn more in the field I was in and doing many different aspect within the field I finally had for a career. Nothing Is Impossible because if you can dream it…see exactly what you want…do the hard work to get there…and then one day, one calm day in a future moment, you will have the opportunity placed in front of you. As they say: If you can see it…you can build it. Just Sayin’

response.answer_text: Yes I believe I can be anything I want to be. Because what I am today started with the belief that I can be that person I want to be. To motivate any one reading this answer, here are five ways you can become the person who you aspire to be: 1. Be authentic. You cannot grow if you are not true to yourself. You have to be honest with yourself about what you are passionate about and who it is you really want to be, despite critics and naysayers. 2. Have vision. People’s dreams perish for lack of vision. Without having the idea in mind of who you want to be, you will not know where or how to aim for it. Keep your vision top of mind as you reach each milestone to motivate you to push forward. 3. Embrace a never-give-up attitude. Curveballs will forever be coming your way as you pursue your dream. You might have moments when you want to throw in the towel because you just can’t keep fighting all the challenges and setbacks you encounter. But you have to push through and realize you really do have everything you need to reach your full potential. 4. Remove the naysayers and self-doubt. Most people settle for less. And many of those same people will also convince you to settle for less. That’s when that self-doubt invades your thoughts. You might have moments when you no longer believe in your dreams—you have to push aside those moments, people and your own self-limiting beliefs. Always move forward. 5. Believe in yourself. As author Richard Bach once wrote, “You are never given a dream without also being given the power to make it true.” So no matter how discouraged you might get at times, you must know that if you can dream something, then you will always have everything in you to make it come true. You just have to believe in yourself and your abilities to achieve what you set your mind to. Hope this helps Regards Kate.

Yes and No. It depends on what context you are asking. You might be able to achieve what you want, but success is not a given. This is a notion instilled into us perhaps by our parents(most parents, at least) about how we’re special. Then we grow up and find that we are in fact, not special. But you can’t wish for impossibilities and want it to happen. You might want to be a time traveler, but that is hardly plausible.      What they mean when they say ‘you can be anything you want’ is ‘believe in yourself to be the best by doing your best’. Its a wonderful notion, if only it wasn’t terribly misinterpreted.  The irony is that we do this to assure ourselves that we can be completely free, but we end up caging ourselves. We are devastated to understand that we can’t be anything, but only our version of that anything. This is not to say we should stop trying. In fact this should inspire us to try harder. ‘you can be anything’ is motivation. What you need is a purpose. And when you find that, you can go on that journey.

response.answer_text: Meet Laurent Duvernay-Tardif.  (Image: Official Website of the Kansas City Chiefs | Chiefs.com) He is just your average NFL Kansas City Chiefs guard player. But he also became the first to earn a Medical doctor degree AND NFL player to become a football player.[1] Now, he made this choice by pushing himself—studying at McGill University while playing football at the university level. When counsellors and family members advised him to choose between sports and studies, he did not let both of his passions down, instead, his wise words were: “It’s all about balance. Don’t give up on your passions!” And I have to admit, you can be anything you want as long as you put in the efforts, have control, balance—and all is good. For example, if I want to become something great, I would have to put in the efforts, have control and find the right balance in order to succeed in life. As BTS’ song would put it “Blood, Sweat, and Tears.” You can be anything you want if you put the right mindset on it. You can read more about him here. Cheers,—Britney Vu Footnotes[1] Is there a doctor in the house? Yes, and he's a pro football player with Chiefs

You cannot be anything you want to be. This answer does not sound right. But it is the answer that people need to know. Those who tell you that you can do anything you want to be are wishing that their words are valid. They too cannot do anything they want to be — and they know it. They can show you a photo of someone who did so many "great" things in life to demonstrate immense possibilities. Someone has done it, so you can too. No, you can't be anything, but you can be the best of what you can be. You cannot be a Michael Jordan, a Tiger Woods, a Steve Jobs, and Elon Musk or a Bill Gates. We can cite millions of names who have done something which you and I cannot be. And I am pretty confident that you can do something and have something most people can't be and cannot do. They don’t have it it takes to be like you. Accept the fact there are many things you cannot do and cannot be. Then you can focus on things that you can do well, on things that can make you happy, and on something that will make your life meaningful. My friend, this is my gift to you today.

Statistically: no. It almost always requires some luck on some level at some point, because no one is in control of all the variables. Do you think you should have the opportunity to be anything you want to be ? Yes, in so far as having access to basic education. Most positions involve competition. Everyone should have the opportunity to compete. Whether you are successful or not is up to you. Lastly there are always some variables that are simply beyond your control. For example you may want to have a career in a specific field, but the market may change such that there is no demand for that position by the time you are ready to enter the field. That’s where the definition of luck comes in: when preparation meets opportunity.

No, but you can be anything you CAN be. Wanting is necessary but not enough. You must evaluate your talent, IQ, physical shape, looks, resources and etc. to determine your potentials. You can raise your bar to a practical and realistic level and challenge yourself. You will have a very happy life when you keep reaching your goals if they are made within reach.
